1. Project Selection & Team Formation
The project selected for this course is "Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System (CIRRS)."
The project aims to address the challenges in managing cybersecurity incidents in organizations by providing a centralized platform for reporting, tracking, and responding to security incidents.
This project was chosen because it addresses a critical real-world problem in cybersecurity management and demonstrates the application of software engineering principles, including system analysis, requirement specification, and design using UML and CASE tools
Team Formation and Assigned Roles
The project team was formed with the following roles and responsibilities:
Team Member	Assigned Role	Responsibilities
Manasa B	Project Manager	Project planning, task allocation, progress tracking, coordination among team members
Ananya Ramesh	Documentation Lead	Preparation of SRS, design documents, reports, and maintaining documentation consistency
Mohan Krishna	Lead Developer 	System design logic, module planning, and technical implementation guidance
J Prethi Chanddana	QA Lead	Requirement verification, review of documents, quality assurance, and validation of system design
These roles ensure clear accountability, efficient workflow, and timely completion of the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System Project.
